        "created_at": "2025-11-08T08:43:21.891Z",
        "cooked": "<p>when the app is set to an RTL language (Hebrew, Arabic), the direction of the typing indicator animation is flipped in the conversation, but not in the chat list.<br>\n<img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/2/2/229316b768180568fec85c501108efb661ef62f6.gif\" alt=\"first\" data-base62-sha1=\"4VRmWTe8i7CL07lowma448JroeW\" width=\"152\" height=\"118\" class=\"animated\"> <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/d/a/da994570d2997993726b58329ff1153874d2a607.gif\" alt=\"second\" data-base62-sha1=\"vbOtbnApmGkhkHhaCrp7zHBUbCT\" width=\"152\" height=\"102\" class=\"animated\"><br>\n(ignore the framerate of the gifs, it’s a conversion artifact, in reality they’re both at the same speed only flipped)<br>\ntyping indicators were originally <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/show-typing-indicators-on-the-right-side-in-rtl-languages/55163\">on the wrong side</a> in conversation, but it seems that the <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-Android/commit/190b9da6c7c85decd9e42e24c00400e71f43a32a\">commit that fixed them</a> originally applied only to the in-convo footer and not to the chat list.</p>",
